                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1r" to="168r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Psalms</title>
                                <note>
                                    <p> Psalms 1-150. The following psalms are give emphasis by an illumination and/or a rubric in gold: 1, 26, 38, 52, 68, 80, 97, 109, 121, 126, 137, 143. The rubric to several of the psalms also contain information about which liturgical hour the psalm belongs to, e.g. Psalm 121 on <locus from="146v" to="146v" scheme="folios"/>: <quote>feria tertia Ad Vesperas</quote>.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="42v" to="42v" scheme="folios"/>: blank.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="168r" to="179v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Canticles</title>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="168r" to="168r" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of Isaias (Isa. 12);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="168v" to="168v" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of Ezechias (Isa. 38:10-20);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="169v" to="169v" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of Anna (1 Kings 2:1-10);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="170v" to="170v" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of Moses (Exod. 15:1-19);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="172r" to="172r" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of Habacuc (Hab. 3:2-19);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="173v" to="173v" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of Moses (Deut. 32:1;</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="177r" to="177r" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of the Three Children (Dan. 3:57-88);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="178r" to="178r" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of Zachary / Benedictus (Luke 1:68-79);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="179r" to="179r" scheme="folios"/>: Canticle of the Blessed Virgin Mary / Magnificat (Luke 1:46-55). <locus from="180" to="180" scheme="folios"/>: ruled, but no text.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
